    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Add Linear-Motion FB</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading2" style="page-break-before:always;">Linear-Motion FB</para>
    <para styleclass="SeeAlso">See also: </para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-FunctionBlock-LinearMotion">Linear Motion dialog</link></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Function-Blocks-Schematic-DataValuesChannels" anchor="HowtoConnectFBs">How to Connect FBs</link></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">Terminology and Definitions</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="2" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:205px;">
          <para styleclass="Interface" style="text-align:right;">Master Machine Angle :<text styleclass="Popup Box2">&#32;</text></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Interface">MMA -<text styleclass="Popup Box"> when you cycle your model, the </text><text styleclass="Popup Box2">MMA</text><text styleclass="Popup Box"> increases at a constant rate from 0 to 360, again and again. You can see and edit the </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small">MMA</text><text styleclass="Popup Box"> at the bottom and left of the application-window.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:205px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box2" style="text-align:right;"><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Linear Motion FB</text> : </para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">The default output from a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Linear-Motion FB</text> is equal to the <text styleclass="Popup Box2">MMA</text>. </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">You can edit the <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Linear-Motion FB</text> to add or subtract a value from the default-output.</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">The <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Linear-Motion FB</text> is usually the first in a series of <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">FBs</text> that you connect together with wires.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">Linear-Motion FB function</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">The function of the <text styleclass="Element">Linear-Motion FB</text> is:</para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName-indent">Output &#160;= MMA <text style="font-size:14pt;">±</text>&#32;<image src="1r.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" style="font-size:8pt; font-weight:normal; vertical-align:sub;" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">MMA = Master-Machine-Angle</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text" style="text-align:left;">Use the <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-FunctionBlock-LinearMotion" styleclass="Element">Linear-Motion dialog</link> to edit <image src="1r.gif" scale="100.00%" style="font-size:7pt; vertical-align:sub;" figurelistinclude="0"></image> .</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
